---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import '../../styles/scenario.css';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Base title="Self-Serve Card Reissue | BlastBox Omega">
  <article class="scenario">
    <div class="container">
      <a href={base} class="back">&larr; All scenarios</a>

      <header class="scenario__header">
        <span class="badge badge--green">Self-serve &middot; Returns &amp; Service Assistant</span>
        <h1>Self-Serve Card Reissue</h1>
        <p class="scenario__lead">
          The gentlest end-to-end shape in the demo: <strong>one MCP lookup, an identity
          check, one state-changing MCP call, and one skill that emits a file</strong>. A
          signed-in member lost their BlastPass card and talks to the assistant directly &mdash;
          no associate in the loop. Nothing changes until they're verified.
        </p>
        <div class="scenario__cast">
          <span class="pill">BlastPass Concierge</span>
          <span class="pill">Membership MCP</span>
          <span class="pill">membership-card-png skill</span>
          <span class="pill">PNG out</span>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section class="convo">
        <h2>The conversation</h2>
        <p class="convo__intro">Member on file: <code>MEGA-BLAST-1024</code> &mdash; Jordan Pixel, BlastPass Plus Extra, console serial <code>OMEGA-7F3A-1024</code>. One capability is spotlighted per turn.</p>

        <ol class="timeline">
          <li class="tl-user">
            <div class="tl-marker">1</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Member (signed in)</div>
              <div class="try-prompt">
                <blockquote class="try-prompt__text">Hi &mdash; I lost my BlastPass card. Can you send me a new one?</blockquote>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="tl-agent">
            <div class="tl-marker">&#9670;</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">BlastPass Concierge</div>
              <div class="tl-steps">
                <p><em>"They want a replacement card. I don't have a membership ID yet, and I can't look anything up &mdash; or verify anyone &mdash; without it. I'll ask for it first; nothing changes until I have it."</em></p>
                <p>"Oh no &mdash; let's get you a new one. 💜 To pull up your membership, what's your <strong>BlastPass member ID</strong>? It usually looks like <code>MEGA-BLAST-####</code>."</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="tl-user">
            <div class="tl-marker">2</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Member</div>
              <div class="try-prompt">
                <blockquote class="try-prompt__text">Sure, it's MEGA-BLAST-1024.</blockquote>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="tl-agent">
            <div class="tl-marker">&#9670;</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">BlastPass Concierge</div>
              <div class="tl-steps">
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">get_membership</span> looks up MEGA-BLAST-1024 (read-only)</div>
                <p>Finds a <strong>BlastPass Plus Extra</strong> membership. Before deactivating a card, the agent verifies identity with <strong>two factors the real owner has</strong> &mdash; and reveals neither.</p>
                <p>"Got it &mdash; I found a Plus Extra membership under that ID. Before I deactivate the old card and issue a new one, I just need to confirm it's really you. Can you give me <strong>two things</strong>: the <strong>name</strong> on the membership, and the <strong>last 4 digits of your console's serial number</strong>?"</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="tl-user">
            <div class="tl-marker">3</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Member</div>
              <div class="try-prompt">
                <blockquote class="try-prompt__text">It's Jordan Pixel, and the last 4 are 1024.</blockquote>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="tl-agent">
            <div class="tl-marker">&#9670;</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">BlastPass Concierge</div>
              <div class="tl-steps">
                <p><em>"Name Jordan Pixel matches, and the serial ends in 1024 &mdash; both factors match. Identity confirmed. Now I can safely reissue."</em></p>
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">reissue_card</span> deactivates the old card, mints a new serial, keeps membership active</div>
                <div class="tl-skill"><span class="tl-skill-name">membership-card-png</span> generates &amp; runs Python (matplotlib)</div>
                <p>Renders a CR80 digital card from the <code>get_membership</code> details plus the freshly minted serial: name, Plus Extra purple tier badge, member ID, console serial, dates, barcode, and perks line.</p>
                <div class="tl-file">&#128196; hands back <strong>blastpass_card.png</strong></div>
                <p>"Thanks, Jordan &mdash; you're verified. ✅ Your new digital card is ready. The old card is now <strong>deactivated</strong>; your tier, term, and BlastPoints are unchanged."</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <div class="result">
          <span class="result__icon">&#129466;</span>
          <div>
            <div class="result__label">Output</div>
            <div class="result__value">blastpass_card.png &mdash; a tier-colored "PLUS EXTRA" digital membership card with the new serial</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>Why it matters</h2>
        <div class="value-grid">
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>Verify before you mutate</h3>
            <p>Identity is confirmed with two factors &mdash; name and last-4 of the serial &mdash; before any card is touched. The agent never reveals either value while asking.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>It actually changes state</h3>
            <p><code>reissue_card</code> deactivates the lost card server-side and mints a new one &mdash; distinct from cancelling the membership. The PNG reflects the new serial, not the old.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>The foundation pattern</h3>
            <p>MCP &rarr; verify &rarr; MCP &rarr; skill &rarr; file is the core loop. The flagship scenario stacks connected agents, policy, and chained math on top of it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>What gets generated</h2>
        <div class="files">
          <div class="filecard">
            <span class="filecard__icon">&#128196;</span>
            <div>
              <strong>blastpass_card.png</strong>
              <span>matplotlib &middot; CR80 card &middot; tier-colored</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
